      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrates discretization error below 5% for hemolysis index QoI.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted with element counts of 1.2M, 3.8M, and 9.6M cells. Richardson extrapolation yielded a discretization error of 3.1% for the normalized index of hemolysis, satisfying the 5% threshold at required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
